 Q&A “Ask an Expert”

 

Question:
    Do you have a comprehensive travel insurance for expats(Non-US citizen) in China going to the US for a summer course program?    
Grace, 
 
06/20/2017





Answer:  Unfortunately, our comprehensive policies are only available to U.S residents who are departing from and returning to their home in the United States.    
    
MattG, 
Customer Care insureMyTrip 

06/26/2017

    
    Was this helpful? 
   

1 person found this helpful.


  Responses


 Respond to question


Question:
    What does waiver of pre-existing condition mean?  I plan to travel on Sept 20 to Europe. I was born on 07 Oct 1941. I have pre-existing health conditions but have been controlled for several years.  I plan to get a comprehensive travel insurance.    
LuzvismindaG, 
 
06/07/2017





Answer:  Most Comprehensive Plans will offer a waiver of pre-existing conditions if you meet the following conditions: You purchase the policy within 10 to 21 days of making your first trip payment; insure ALL prepaid non-refundable expenses prior to your departure date; and be medically fit to travel the day you purchase the policy.  If the reason you are canceling, interrupting or seeking medical coverage is related to pre-existing conditions there will be no coverage, unless you have the waiver.  A Pre-Existing Condition is any treatment, diagnostic tests or exams, any recommendations for diagnostic test or exams, or any adjustments in medication up or down within the pre-existing condition period stated (depending on the company, 60 – 180 days prior to the effective date).      
    
MattG, 
Customer Care insureMyTrip 

06/10/2017

    
    Was this helpful? 
   

1 person found this helpful.


