Question:
    My wife and I are traveling to Orlando, FL July 1-8 to attend grandson's baseball team tournament play.  The airfare will be booked by us while the rooms at Disney are being booked by the team and we will have to reimburse them for that cost.  Will trip insurance cover that portion of the trip if it is not paid directly to Disney by us?    
Bryon, 
 
05/17/2017





Answer:  Yes, as long as you can prove that you reimbursed the travel supplier for the cost of the accommodations, you can insure that travel arrangement provided that it is prepaid and non-refundable.      
    
