Question:
    If you arrange your own air using miles, what's the best way to protect yourself against fees for redepositing/changing?  Cost of the trip is not in dollars, but miles and fees.    
Melody, 
 
02/07/2014





Answer:  Airline miles are not generally considered an insurable cost. The fees and taxes you pay to use them can be insured for, and certain companies will also allow you to insure the cost of re-banking or re-depositing fees. There is also one company - Travel Insured - who will allow you to insure the value of the tickets, as long as the airline does NOT allow you to re-bank the miles.    
    
David M., 
Customer Care insureMyTrip 

02/07/2014

    
