Question:
    We travel several times each year to various places and don't have a lot of equipment, etc.  Mainly just want a policy that will cover major medical situations for the whole year, just in case, since we are 62 years old (although we are healthy and active now).  Is it better to buy a separate evac policy?  Is there a good option that we have not thought of?    
Trisha, 
 
03/18/2017





Answer:  We do provide annual medical policies for trips that take place outside of your home country.  Typically, the trips cannot be longer than 90 days per trip with most plans.

To obtain a quote, please fill out the quote form with your very first trip's details and once you arrive on the results page, please select the medical tab and view our plans that are labeled “multi trip".  Our multi-trip medical plans provide both medical and medical evacuation coverage.  You do not need to buy a separate evacuation policy unless you wanted the extra coverage.     
    
MattG, 
Customer Care insureMyTrip 

03/21/2017

    
