Question:
    1)  what are "covered reasons" for CFAR policies?

2)  i'm approaching the 14 day timeframe to purchase CFAR policy.  Are there any other options available?    
PB, 
 
04/29/2014





Answer:  Cancel for any reason does not use covered reasons. The CFAR benefit lets you change your mind about the trip, doesn't matter what for. And yes, there are other plans that allow 21 days for cancel for any reason. If you get a quote on our website, there will be a filter available to only show the options with cancel for any reason.    
    
David M., 
Customer Care insureMyTrip 

04/29/2014

    
